00:33:53,567 --> 00:33:55,767
Now that technology
only allows you to see,

574
00:33:57,033 --> 00:33:58,433
so how are you here?

575
00:33:59,133 --> 00:34:01,900
- I want you to understand
why, moreso than how.

576
00:34:01,900 --> 00:34:03,867
- You gotta understand
that a man of reason

577
00:34:03,867 --> 00:34:07,000
the things you're telling me
are all impossible to accept.

578
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:08,167
I understand.

579
00:34:08,867 --> 00:34:10,300
- I've studied all this.

580
00:34:10,300 --> 00:34:11,733
I've fantasized about it.

581
00:34:11,733 --> 00:34:13,300
I mean, most scientists,

582
00:34:13,300 --> 00:34:16,867
people like Albert Einstein--

583
00:34:16,867 --> 00:34:17,700
- Hawking.

584
00:34:17,700 --> 00:34:19,100
- Stephen Hawking.

585
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:21,333
They don't even believe
something like this is possible,

586
00:34:21,333 --> 00:34:23,467
yet you're sitting
here telling me

587
00:34:23,467 --> 00:34:25,667
that you're actually living
proof that it exists.

588
00:34:25,667 --> 00:34:27,100
- Yes, I am.

589
00:34:28,100 --> 00:34:30,767
- The idea of taking a man,
or a woman, from one time

590
00:34:30,767 --> 00:34:33,000
and putting them into another
that already happened?

591
00:34:34,267 --> 00:34:37,333
It, there's just so many
questions that arise from that.

592
00:34:37,333 --> 00:34:39,500
- I was as skeptical as
you are when I began.

593
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:43,233
- Okay, one of the biggest
issues that comes up

594
00:34:43,233 --> 00:34:45,133
right away is causality.

595
00:34:45,133 --> 00:34:47,267
So if you change something
in the past, then...

596
00:34:47,867 --> 00:34:49,500
- The grandfather
paradox is something

597
00:34:49,500 --> 00:34:51,200
we all debated for a long time.

598
00:34:51,200 --> 00:34:54,033
If Jimmy goes back into the
past and kills his grandma,

599
00:34:54,867 --> 00:34:57,233
will Jimmy or his
family ever exist?

600
00:34:57,233 --> 00:34:58,100
- Right.

601
00:34:58,533 --> 00:34:59,733
So,

602
00:34:59,867 --> 00:35:01,933
- I came to two
conclusions about time.

603
00:35:01,933 --> 00:35:03,300
Many theories existed.

604
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:05,600
But now I could
eliminate the arguments

605
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:07,133
that travel wasn't possible.

606
00:35:07,767 --> 00:35:10,067
Or that only forward travel was.

607
00:35:10,767 --> 00:35:12,500
I did tests and experiments

608
00:35:12,500 --> 00:35:14,367
that lead me to
two possibilities.

609
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:17,633
Either time was
circular, constant,

610
00:35:17,633 --> 00:35:20,900
or when you went back it
would create an offshoot.

611
00:35:20,900 --> 00:35:22,533
- Like a separate timeline.

612
00:35:22,533 --> 00:35:24,067
- That's right, a
new branch of time,

613
00:35:24,067 --> 00:35:27,133
moving forward, parallel
to the original,

614
00:35:27,133 --> 00:35:29,000
with its own events
and outcomes.

615
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:30,500
- So which is it?

616
00:35:31,333 --> 00:35:32,733
- A definitive answer
to that question

617
00:35:32,733 --> 00:35:34,000
is close to impossible.

618
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:36,867
Even if Jimmy goes and
kills his grandfather

619
00:35:36,867 --> 00:35:39,167
and wipes out his whole
family in the process,

620
00:35:39,167 --> 00:35:43,200
does time ultimately find
its way to the same outcome?

621
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:47,367
Or is it set in a new
direction, a new course?

622
00:35:47,367 --> 00:35:49,333
Or does the original
future coexist

623
00:35:49,333 --> 00:35:52,100
with a separate timeline
that Jimmy created?

624
00:35:52,100 --> 00:35:54,467
Or, does Jimmy fail?

625
00:35:55,533 --> 00:35:57,700
Maybe if Jimmy tried
to do something

626
00:35:57,700 --> 00:36:01,467
as significant as kill his
grandfather in the past,

627
00:36:01,467 --> 00:36:04,133
time or fate would not allow it.

628
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:07,633
The gun would jam.

629
00:36:08,867 --> 00:36:10,600
Or a bird would get in the way.

630
00:36:25,767 --> 00:36:26,867
- I don't understand.

631
00:36:26,867 --> 00:36:28,700
So, if you're from the future,

632
00:36:29,633 --> 00:36:31,367
theoretically a time
far after Jimmy would've

633
00:36:31,367 --> 00:36:33,900
killed his grandfather wouldn't
you see the changes it made?

634
00:36:35,367 --> 00:36:36,700
- It's not that simple, Doctor.

635
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:41,767
Firstly, only the
traveler would ever know.

636
00:36:41,767 --> 00:36:44,067
If time had changed, we
would never experience it.

637
00:36:44,733 --> 00:36:47,600
To us, Jimmy never existed.

638
00:36:48,433 --> 00:36:51,400
- Okay, okay, what if someobdy
went back and killed Hitler?

